questions.question: Which columns in the dataset have a high proportion of missing values, say above 5%? Return as JSON with keys: count, columns.
questions.hint: Calculate the missing percentage for each column and list those exceeding the threshold.
questions.output_schema: A JSON object with exactly 2 keys: "count" (integer) and "columns" (list of column names, alphabetically sorted). Example: {"count": 3, "columns": ["col_a", "col_b", "col_c"]}

questions.question: Are there any columns in this dataset that have a large fraction of missing values? Return as JSON with keys: count, columns.
questions.hint: Compute the missing percentage for each column and list those where it exceeds 10%.
questions.output_schema: A JSON object with exactly 2 keys: "count" (integer) and "columns" (list of column names, alphabetically sorted). Example: {"count": 3, "columns": ["col_a", "col_b", "col_c"]}
